sudo
  runas admin

apt-get
  used for various tools to do things

sudo apt-get update
  check for latest update packages
sudo apt-get upgrade
  install all upgrade packages
history
  see history for inputs on terminal

use python3
$ environment variable stores home folder

explorer.exe .
  opens explorer (the . tells it to run where i am in directory)

python3 --version
  checks for version of python(or other installs just replace python)
sudo apt-get install python3
  install for python3

sudo apt-get install python3-pip
  install pip

python3 -m pip install --user --upgrade pip
  install latest packages

 sudo apt-get install python3.8-venv
  install virtual environment

python3 -m venv .venv
  create new virtual environment

. .venv/bin/activate
  activate virtual environment

sudo curl -o /usr/local/bin/atom #URL
  tells the terminal to store data taken from a url in the given path

sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/atom
  changes which groups(owner,users, public) can read,execute or write files/folders

atom .

  run atom using my current directory

sudo chown -R jon:jon code
  changes ownership of files and folders.
  -R means using recursive(will run through the files and open folders to run through the files in the folders aswell)

source .venv/bin/activate
  starting venv, sourse tells it to use all the packages from the source Code

ctrl+r
  reverse search for inputs in history

tab to autofill possible inputs

