   git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
    code to confiure github to my account

    git commit -m "My First Commit"
     commit to github and give it a Name

    git log
      see log notes of commits

    git status
      see the status of the repository

  ssh key process
    ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "jonrw97@gmail.com"
    eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
    ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
    cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
    ssh -T git@github.com

  Push files to github
    nano .git/config (change url to git@githun.com:Jonrw97/#repositoryname#.git)
    git branch -M main
    git push -u origin main

      ssh key is advanced authentication for github to connect to your computer

